  ==
::
::  BASELINE TESTS (commented out - already verified current behavior)
::  These established that 50 fail and 50 succeed with the current broken code
::
::++  test-baseline-failures
::  ::  Test that all 50 failure cases currently produce WRONG hashes
::  %-  expect
::  !>
::  =/  results=(list ?)
::    %+  turn  initially-failed-cases
::    |=  [h=@ud raw=@t expected=@uvI]
::    =/  header=block-header  (parse-raw-to-header raw h)
::    =/  computed=@uvI  computed-hash.header
::    !=(computed expected)  :: Should NOT match
::  (levy results same)
::
::++  test-baseline-successes
::  ::  Test that all 50 success cases currently produce CORRECT hashes
::  %-  expect
::  !>
::  =/  results=(list ?)
::    %+  turn  initially-succeeded-cases
::    |=  [h=@ud raw=@t expected=@uvI]
::    =/  header=block-header  (parse-raw-to-header raw h)
::    =/  computed=@uvI  computed-hash.header
::    =(computed expected)  :: Should match
::  (levy results same)
::
::  TDD GOAL TESTS: All 100 cases should produce correct hashes after fix
::
++  test-all-initially-failed-now-pass
  ::  After fixing the bug, all 50 "failure" cases should now PASS
  ::  (produce correct hashes matching network)
  %-  expect
  !>
  =/  results=(list ?)
    %+  turn  initially-failed-cases
    |=  [h=@ud raw=@t expected=@uvI]
    =/  header=block-header  (parse-raw-to-header raw h)
    =/  computed=@uvI  computed-hash.header
    =(computed expected)  :: Should now MATCH
  (levy results same)
::
++  test-all-initially-succeeded-still-pass
  ::  After fixing the bug, all 50 "success" cases should STILL PASS
  ::  (continue to produce correct hashes)
  %-  expect
  !>
  =/  results=(list ?)
    %+  turn  initially-succeeded-cases
    |=  [h=@ud raw=@t expected=@uvI]
    =/  header=block-header  (parse-raw-to-header raw h)
    =/  computed=@uvI  computed-hash.header
    =(computed expected)  :: Should still MATCH
  (levy results same)
::
++  test-chain-linkage
  ::  REGRESSION TEST: Verify consecutive blocks link correctly
  ::  Block N+1's prev-hash must match block N's computed hash
  ::
  ::  This test prevents regression of the field extraction bug where
  ::  cut positions were not adjusted for flipped byte order, causing
  ::  prev-hash to extract wrong bytes from the header atom.
  ::
  ::  Tests multiple consecutive block pairs from different heights
  %-  expect
  !>
  =/  test-pairs=(list [h1=@ud r1=@t h2=@ud r2=@t])
    :~  ::  Blocks 4,000,000-4,000,001
        :^  4.000.000
          '0000002338a7b82f7952c32ac285b473ca02ec400faff1b68b82162e53000000000000007ea78d3e9a91364fb33bcc1e8aad2de68cd6a2f482e2855fe1381a2bc7db77d42009c767fcff031a60c19a66'
          4.000.001
          '00000024aead64270b364766c2de42a29d87f344f929c0ec7ca4a647390300000000000025d198cfff2be0369dfbfed96b2060ae923edf4267365891d53d2e85a0668b532009c767fcff031a1338acfd'
        ::  Blocks 4,300,000-4,300,001
        :^  4.300.000
          '000013214963b2cd8695c797a4ab884037bcb0031a71436405ba42e18d800c02000000006396f08ec2fffe7db97845f408d69c129d76eb1ff8c76bd02de4331439c66aa034381068c0ff3f199846a83f'
          4.300.001
          '00a0b820ce1aa60fb2be219dfb964c9bbd1ffe44f801d76bd98605c80e00000000000000b129364d12acc8e49b3286824c16e976ffce72e1e8106cfe964e738b5b1120f1e53c1068ffff001d6201fcba'
        ::  Blocks 4,520,001-4,520,002
        :^  4.520.001
          '00e0fb32e7e1e4f8ea33547359d34bdbebc22deb1c371c5e21dd43963a2a0400000000004d50d33a7201acbbfc243f08d306ab1afa7e46b27c4632de12b087f5af39ac59cbbe52682478071bbd276989'
          4.520.002
          '00e07e3004cb852d4341e33cc24df7e741712b0fdccde25510cd0e27890a00000000000012235649d3f97b0d3b72b8280562b2e63a760884c1f0923ffb99dc2e8b46b62ccbbe52682478071b70f321df'
    ==
  ::
  =/  results=(list ?)
    %+  turn  test-pairs
    |=  [h1=@ud r1=@t h2=@ud r2=@t]
    =/  header-1=block-header  (parse-raw-to-header r1 h1)
    =/  header-2=block-header  (parse-raw-to-header r2 h2)
    =/  hash-1=@uvI  computed-hash.header-1
    =/  prev-hash-2=@uvI  prev-hash.header-2
    =(hash-1 prev-hash-2)
  ::
  (levy results same)
::
::  Merkle Proof Tests
::  Using real transaction data from Bitcoin testnet
::  Data source: mempool.space API
::  All hashes verified against blockchain.info and mempool.space
::
::  Real transaction from block 4,000,000
::  TXID: 6b423c8e551a0922db07e6a9d345996ed5a5dfb96cfae0959b82e4dbcd826b80
::  Block merkle root: d477dbc72b1a38e15f85e282f4a2d68ce62dad8a1ecc3bb34f36919a3e8da77e
::  Position: 0 (leftmost transaction in merkle tree)
::
::  Merkle tree structure (512 transactions, 9 levels):
::  Level 0: txid (position 0) - hashes converted from display to internal byte order
::  Level 1-9: each level hashes current with sibling using internal byte order
::  Final result converted back to display format for comparison with block header
::
++  test-merkle-proof-block-4000000
  %-  expect
  !>
  =/  txid=@t  '6b423c8e551a0922db07e6a9d345996ed5a5dfb96cfae0959b82e4dbcd826b80'
  =/  merkle=(list @t)
    :~  '26d971fca7b727cb326dc6dd5b36f2bc4aa83b6f865055b313e0df0a994a947f'
        '49fd0efba77872797ca2097d39d76ba7f559e316a09da2bc2438f728dcd172e9'
        'be086253b45f06bfa3e259bda1020fc96f9a45874cf80891738680f5c67ffe38'
        'f89b1255ad428455e02993eb5431ef8ccf5e6542e7e2da3e9b02a9b8a228f0cb'
        '5f026da03c1e9706711037e6e422ee534339c0422fe94c788ec9f154c91e0fab'
        'fac7aa0ac5e8f4754afe25e39cd4de2bc68284b26a86604636cee855d56550d6'
        '44943245a7f31135302499311b1da7c7873a9ccc1292b60b80cfe8826ca11e64'
        'cec81bae46fadfd96e6f4092ae87f1061301341fc8999e7aa3e7dd1adf25c991'
        'ecd5967be16ac4bb842e901692b40309ae3d347ce934e1a81e4725012162c359'
    ==
  =/  pos=@  0
  =/  expected-root=@t  'd477dbc72b1a38e15f85e282f4a2d68ce62dad8a1ecc3bb34f36919a3e8da77e'
  ::
  (verify-merkle-proof txid merkle pos expected-root)
::
::  NOTE: Individual step tests removed because bitcoin-hash expects
::  hashes in internal byte order. The verify-merkle-proof function
::  handles the conversion from display format to internal format.
::
::  Test merkle proof at position 14 (not leftmost)
::  Block 4,749,817 - TXID at position 14
::  This tests a different merkle path with RIGHT siblings
::
++  test-merkle-proof-block-4749817-pos-14
  %-  expect
  !>
  =/  txid=@t  '89a5bf34d3fe6f4d8a4bb88657153a42dbf771e7adeb83bbf9534b8ed37f329c'
  =/  merkle=(list @t)
    :~  'a410c0d6f0df324fc65cc71b575653ebc58ef4524a305226901038a90202c5f8'
        '52fa520bf4adaa8e5c8e4ae4107c64f8f3e3fa9698caf007596dedfc4ebdbd59'
        'b839c24f2caab067fd9772640dfd92e405d4790b10a26cb9c5a4edff3b93b98b'
        '448075179e1b91fceb3fbaf7b5812587deee9be56bfd8d9ce761b7ddf7e6a92e'
        'f571079f3b0e23f776b35f00dcb6265a52b40f3f7a7026b91bf10653d370b94a'
    ==
  =/  pos=@  14
  =/  expected-root=@t  '284b58d7d279e91453de3c901171ef045407022e48f427576f961001850b6d74'
  ::
  (verify-merkle-proof txid merkle pos expected-root)
